Project Dependency Graph

Dependency Tree

  • net.automatalib:automata-examples:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial
    AutomataLib :: Examples

    Description: A collection of various small example applications that illustrate several use cases of AutomataLib.<br /> <em>Note:</em> This artifact is not intended as a library, but only exists for educational purposes.

    URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-examples/

    Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-api:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: API

      Description: This artifact contains the API of AutomataLib, which mainly consists of interfaces for the various concepts and automaton models supported by the AutomataLib core. In addition to that, it also defines some fundamental classes for dealing with words of symbols.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-api/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

      • net.automatalib:automata-commons-util:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
        AutomataLib :: Commons :: Utilities

        Description: Basic utility library containing several useful classes (e.g., a Pair class) to ease everyday programming.

        URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-commons-parent/automata-commons-util/

        Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

        • com.google.guava:guava:jar:15.0 (compile)
          Guava: Google Core Libraries for Java

          Description: Guava is a suite of core and expanded libraries that include utility classes, google's collections, io classes, and much much more. Guava has two code dependencies - javax.annotation per the JSR-305 spec and javax.inject per the JSR-330 spec.

          URL: http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/guava

          Project License: The Apache Software License, Version 2.0

    • net.automatalib:automata-core:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Core

      Description: The core artifact of AutomataLib. This library contains concrete implementations for many of the automaton model interfaces defined in the API artifact, as well as abstract base classes that facilitate implementing new automaton model classes. Note that concrete algorithms (traversal, reachability analysis etc.) are not in the scope of this artifact.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-core/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-commons-dotutil:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Commons :: DOT Utilities

      Description: This utility artifact contains methods that facilitate interaction with the <a href="http://www.graphviz.org/">GraphVIZ DOT</a> tool, and allows to render and display DOT models directly from within the application.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-commons-parent/automata-commons-dotutil/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-util:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Utilities

      Description: This artifact provides various common utility operations for analyzing and manipulating automata and graphs, such as traversal, minimization and copying.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-util/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

      • net.automatalib:automata-commons-smartcollections:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
        AutomataLib :: Commons :: Smart Collections

        Description: This library provides efficient implementations for various collection data structures (esp. linked lists and priority queues), which have very insufficient implementation in the Java Collections Foundations that makes it hard or even impossible to exploit their efficiencies.

        URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-commons-parent/automata-commons-smartcollections/

        Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-incremental:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Misc :: Incremental

      Description: A library for incremental automata construction. This artifact contains algorithms for incrementally constructing DFAs (both prefix-closed and non-prefix-closed) and Mealy machines from a finite, incrementally growing set of example inputs/outputs.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-misc-parent/automata-incremental/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-brics:jar:0.3.1-ase2013-tutorial (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Adapters :: BRICS

      Description: This artifact contains adapter classes for treating the <tt>Automaton</tt> objects from the <a href="http://www.brics.dk/automaton">BRICS library</a> as AutomataLib models.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/automata-adapters-parent/automata-brics/

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • dk.brics.automaton:automaton:jar:1.11-8 (compile)
      Automaton

      Description: A DFA/NFA (finite-state automata) implementation with Unicode alphabet (UTF16) and support for the standard regular expression operations (concatenation, union, Kleene star) and a number of non-standard ones (intersection, complement, etc.)

      URL: http://www.brics.dk/automaton/

      Project License: BSD
